                    <msContents>
                        <summary>It registers the gift of Nallūr and surrounding villages, consisting in 360 <foreign>vēli</foreign>s of land, as well as the revenue in taxes from these lands, for the food offerings <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiruppaṭimāṟu</foreign></supplied> and the sacred service <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiruppaṇi</foreign></supplied>. The donor is the chieftain Āḷappiṟantāṉ Mōkaṉ, alias Kaṭavarāyaṉ.       
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
